In the opera category, Berg's "Lulu" of the Royal Opera House Orchestra; Adolf Hates "Marc Antonio e Cleopatra" of Ars Lyrica Houston; Kaija Saariaho's "L'Amour de Loin" of the German Symphony Orchestra Berlin; and Rodion Shchedrin's "The Enchanted Wanderer" of the Orchestra and Choir of the Mariinsky Theatre; and Arthur Sullivan's "Ivanhoe" of the BBC National Orchestra of Wales were nominated.
As composers, Pärt was nominated for Symphony No. 4, Daugherty for "Deus Ex Machina," Hans Werner Henze for "Appassionatamente Plus," Magnus Lindberg for "Graffiti" and Shchedrin for "The Enchanted Wanderer" for a Grammy.
Pärt's Symphony No. 4 was premiered and recorded at Disney Hall on January 4 by the L.A. Philharmonic under the direction of Esa-Pekka Salonen.
The 30-minute piece is entitled "Los Angeles" and is dedicated to the former oil magnate Mikhail Chodorkovsky, who is in prison in Russia.
