The US changes the rules for receiving a visa
The persons must present themselves to the services for visa applications before their meeting with the consulate; costs will be reduced in this way.
As from 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa will change at the Embassy of the United States and in the consulates.
In the new procedure, most of the applicants have to present themselves to the visa application services (ASC, the initial letters in English) before they have been discussed at the consulate.
The staff of the ASC shall record the applicant's biometric data, which shall be verified by the consulate before the interview.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of the processing of the visa is reduced because it is no longer necessary to pay separately the appointment, the processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is issued.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the equivalent of 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including temporary visas) and 390 dollars for traders and investors.
Those who only want to extend their visa do not have to have a conversation at the consulate, they only have to imagine at the nearest ASC where they will present their documents and take their fingerprints.
As the biometric data is collected in the ASC, the applicants who need a second date for the consultation in the consulate remain there less time than before.
Those who apply for the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer have to pay the service surcharge of 26 dollars.
For more information on the new visa application procedure, see the following website: http: / / mexico.usembassy.gov / boletines / sp101201 _ Visas-FAQs.html
